# Biotech Stock Scanner вЂ” Implementation Plan

A Next.js web app that scans the stock market for biotech stocks exhibiting a slow, steady price rise (3вЂ“12 months) using linear regression analysis. Stocks are ranked by RВІ (consistency) and slope (growth rate).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Key Required**: You'll need to provide your FMP API key as an environment variable (`FMP_API_KEY`). The starter tier gives us **300 requests/min** and **20 GB/month bandwidth** вЂ” sufficient for scanning ~500 biotech stocks daily.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Setup**: We'll need a Neon Postgres connection string and an Upstash Redis URL+token. Please confirm you have these or want me to help set them up.

> [!WARNING]
> **Yahoo Finance as Fallback**: The `yahoo-finance2` package uses unofficial endpoints that can break. We use it as a fallback only when FMP is rate-limited, not as the primary source.

